  "articleSummary": "The article argues that the native Fetch API is now capable enough to replace Axios for most HTTP use cases, providing a feature comparison table showing fetch can handle interceptors, cancellation, progress, and streaming. It offers a tutorial-style collection of code recipes for common tasks like JSON handling, file uploads, timeouts, and retries, noting that fetch requires manual JSON parsing/stringifying. The intended audience is developers evaluating whether to use Axios or other HTTP libraries. The tone is advocacy and instructional, not confrontational, framed around the idea that \"you may not need\" third-party libraries.",
